  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Driver",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Drive the company van and lorries to run errands and ferry visitors and employees.</li>\n  <li>Collect/dispatch of documents/parcels and any items as required.</li>\n  <li>Ferry staff to/from the site office, training centres, medical appointments and lunch.</li>\n  <li>Monitor servicing schedules and all administrative matters pertaining to the vehicle and report them to the Admin Manager.</li>\n  <li>Ensure cleanliness and proper maintenance of the van.</li>\n  <li>Perform any other tasks as may be assigned by the supervisor.</li>\n  <li>Comply with all the workplace traffic rules and regulations.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with relevant government regulations and the company’s quality, safety, health and environmental (QSHE) policies, practices and procedures at all times.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Possess a valid class 3 and class 4 licence; a vocational licence will be an advantage.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 3 years of relevant working experience in a similar industry.</li>\n  <li>Clean driving record and familiarity with Singapore roads.</li>\n  <li>Good interpersonal and communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Physically fit to be able to maintain the cleanliness of the vehicles.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Note: Company vehicles cannot be driven home.</p>",
